Collection logReleased6 December 2018 (Update)Also calledColl logMembersNoQuest itemNoPropertiesTradeableNoEquipableNoStackableNoNoteableNoOptionsRead, DestroyDestroyYou can get another from The Collector in Varrock museum.ExamineA record of rewards and loot obtained all throughout Gielinor.ValuesValue6 coinsHigh alch3 coinsLow alch2 coinsWeight0.51 kgAdvanced dataItem ID22711

The collection log is a book that players can receive from The Collector near the stairs in the Varrock Museum's ground floor[UK]1st floor[US]. It records nearly every unique drop the player has obtained from various content in Old School RuneScape. The player does not need to have claimed a collection log for it to start tracking drops.

Drops obtained prior to its release are not recorded for any player, excluding untradeable items (such as pets) provided that they can be tracked by the game; for example, long bones the player had traded to Barlak or buried before the log's release were not added to it, but any long bones in the player's possession were added.

Each entry in the log is tracked by the item itself, not where it was obtained. This means that collection log item slots can be shared across multiple pages. For example, obtaining a dragon pickaxe from the Chaos Elemental will also log it under other bosses that drop it, such as Callisto and the King Black Dragon.

There is a cap on the amount each item can be tracked, depending on the item in question. For example, Zulrah's scales will only be tracked up to 65,535 and bracelets of ethereum up to 250.

It can be stored in a bookcase within a player-owned house, and can also be accessed from the adventurer's log within a player's Achievement Gallery and the Character Summary interface.

There are currently a total of 1,715 slots to fill in the collection log, with a total of 1,524 unique entries being tracked. Pets, gilded equipment, and 3rd age equipment account for 123 of the 191 slots containing duplicate items.

Date Changes 6 March 2024

(update)

Search result categories can now be clicked to view additional information for the entire category.

Search result category names can now be clicked to navigate to the main page for the category.

16 August 2023

(update)

Fixed a bug where certain items were being skipped or displaying incorrectly in the collection log. Players affected by this issue should find the issues resolved upon their next log in.

Fixed a bug with collection log values related to Larran's big chest, the Brimstone chest, and the Gauntlet.

3 August 2023

(update)

Duke Sucellus, The Leviathan, The Whisperer and Vardorvis had the Awakener's orb added to their collection log.

26 July 2023

(update)

The following bosses from Desert Treasure II were added to the collection log:

Duke Sucellus

The Leviathan

The Whisperer

Vardorvis

12 July 2023

(update)

The collection log for Forestry now includes the lumberjack outfit.

Forestry is now in the correct alphabetical position in the Other section of the collection log, rather than the very bottom.

5 July 2023

(update)

Rewards received from Forestry now appear in the collection log.

29 June 2022

(update)

The Combat Achievement button in the collection log is now in the same place no matter which category is selected.

4 May 2022

(update)

Added the Tarnished Locket and the Lost Bag to the collection log. They will retroactively unlock for anyone who's already received them as drops.

12 January 2022

(update)

Nexling now correctly shows up in the collection log.

17 November 2021

(update)

The collection log entry for Penance Gloves will now update on login and when opening the Log.

28 April 2021

(update)

Some new counters have been added to the collection log, including the number of Tempoross Reward Permits claimed, and Spoils Of War opened in Soul Wars!

14 April 2021

(update)

Brimhaven graceful pieces will now be correctly counted within the collection log on log-in.

A new counter shows the total number of unique items obtained.

Added a toggleable chat/popup notification when a new item has been added to the collection log.

Pirate Hook has been moved from Underwater Agility to the Brimhaven Agility section.

Merfolk Trident has been added to the Misc section.

Marks of Grace have been added to the Rooftop Agility section.

Third age pieces now have their own separate tab.
